Senior Service Manager Job
GE
Date: Apr 30, 2014
Location: Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates
Job Number: 1957129
Business: GE Aviation
Business Segment: Aviation
About Us: At GE Aviation, we are imagination at work. Whether we’re manufacturing components for our GEnx engines or driving innovation in fuel and noise reduction, the GE Aviation teams are dedicated to turning imaginative ideas into advances in aviation that solve some of the world’s toughest problems. Join us and you’ll find yourself in a dynamic environment where our ongoing, substantial investment in research and development keeps us moving forward and looking ahead. At GE, developing people is embedded in our culture and integral to our growth. Here you’ll work collaboratively and across functions with the highest caliber talent, utilizing cutting-edge technology and processes. Whether it’s the next generation of ecomagination products or the future of aircraft engines, we’ve got the state-of-the-art resources to make those innovations a reality. If you’re passionate about aviation and looking for a career rich with challenges and unlimited opportunities for growth and advancement, then join GE in reengineering the sky through aviation innovations that will impact the globe for generations to come.
Posted Position Title: Senior Service Manager
Career Level: Experienced
Function: Services
Function Segment: Field Services
Location: United Arab Emirates
U.S. State, China or Canada Provinces:
City: Abu Dhabi
Postal Code:
Relocation Assistance: Yes
Role Summary/Purpose: **This position is based in UAE**The Senior Service Manager works independently and will provide direction to team of Field service engineers on providing high quality technical advice & assistance to assigned customers on the safe, reliable and cost effective operation of our aviation engines.
This position also serves as an expert resource for our customers and business for multiple product lines and disciplines.
Essential Responsibilities: As Senior Service Manager based in Abu Dhabi, you will:Provide expert technical advice to customers and GE colleagues and stakeholdersImprove quality of regional Technical reviews for assigned region & engine familiesUse Lean Six Sigma, reliability and other analytical skills to ensure optimum performance & reliability of products operated and maintained by assigned customers.
Mentor GE Field service team on the analytical skills/tools required to meet airline customer expectationsApply interpersonal, technical and business skills to drive overall customer satisfaction & product performance to enhance GE business growthTrain and mentor customers on the use of engine trend diagnostics.
Utilize GE diagnostics tools and trend data to proactively identify imminent engine malfunctions and opportunities for improvement in customer engine reliability and cost of ownershipDemonstrate significant comprehensive technical understanding of the operation, maintenance, & trouble-shooting of assigned engine programs.
Use technical knowledge to influence new product design & programsReview reported malfunctions & assist with fault analysisUtilize aircraft and engine systems interactions as required to troubleshoot and rectify fault messages and operational complaintsReview effectiveness of maintenance actions to identify training needs & improve maintenance practicesFor high priority modification programs, assist customer and GE ensuring equipment & parts are available to meet schedules.
Lead as regional focal point and report out to region managers as requiredMonitor test cell operations & RFI planning as required.Assist the factory with data collection & timely reporting to facilitate performance analysis, provide marketing intelligence, & sales opportunities for programs, services, & supportUnderstand the operation of business collaboration and other systems and tools to assist the customer in areas such as spare parts ordering, issues resolution, provisioning, & other business processes.
Qualifications/Requirements: Bachelor’s degree from an accredited university or collegeAt least 5 additional years of experience in Field ServicesAt least 3 years of experience in a management roleExperience working in a matrixed organization with stakeholders located globallyWillingness and ability to travel within assigned region
Additional Eligibility Qualifications:
Desired Characteristics:
Bachelor’s degree in Engineering or physical science is preferred
Six Sigma GB trained
Strong business acumen and commercial savvy
Ability to manage effectively in a dynamic and fast-paced environment
Strong customer service mindset
Effective team contributor and member
Ability to energize teams through inclusiveness and connection with people
Working knowledge of contract terms and conditions
Familiarity with project labor and material quoting tools
Ability to build trust by respecting the ideas and contributions of everyone
Strong oral and written communication skills
Strong interpersonal and leadership skills
Job Segments: Service Manager, Engineer, Lean Six Sigma, Manager, Marketing Manager, Customer Service, Engineering, Management, Marketing
